{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, a real pathologist reduced the number of normal tissue slides examined by 90.0% using vPatho, while only a single slide was missing from 1028 examined slides from 136 patients.",
    "At the case level, we identified 7 erroneous cases per 100 cases.",
    "When false sorting occurred in patients with 8 whole-mount slides on average, at least one slide was falsely sorted.",
    "When we examined the causes of these errors, we found that one of the 7 patients had a false negative slide, whereas the remaining 6 patients had at least one false positive slide.",
    "The error rate for falsely sorted slides in affected patients was 14% (range: 11-29%), which was significantly greater than the overall error rate for examined slides (1%)."
  ]
}